{
  "title": "148863946.this That And The Other Thing",
  "slug": "148863946this-that-and-the-other-thing",
  "publishedAt": "2025-11-30T19:30:10.554Z",
  "excerpt": "Something you slowly pick up on when relying on your circumstances to make decisions for you is that good reasons for not doing what you know you should do tend to pop up everywhere.",
  "image": "",
  "readTime": "1 min",
  "content": [
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Something you slowly pick up on when relying on your circumstances to make decisions for you is that good reasons for",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "not",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "doing what you know you should do tend to pop up everywhere.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "That’s because our focus is often what becomes our reality. If you’re actively looking for excuses, there’s no possible way to avoid them.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "The trick is to acknowledge that you’re looking for them because",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "you want to",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ".",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Because",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "finding excuses",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "is a way to avoid doing the work required to have the things we want.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Actions that are often fraught with fear, or apathy, or inertia.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Acknowledging the feelings behind your postponement is how to acknowledge",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "why",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "you’re stalling.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "A precursor to discovering what you can do about it.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}